29/03/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Nineteen customs officers were convicted of corruption on Monday (March 28th) and sentenced to four years in prison each.
The officers, who worked at one of the airports in Bucharest, were found guilty of over 8,000 incidents of corruption between December 2005 and September 2006.
The court ruling can be appealed.
(Ziare, Cotidianul, Realitatea - 28/03/11)
